Description
-----------
AdPlay/Linux is AdPlug's Linux/FreeBSD console-based frontend.

Prerequisites
-------------
The following libraries and/or programs are needed in order to compile this
program:

Program/Library		Version
---------------		-------
glibc			>= 2.1
adplug			>= 1.1

Installation
------------
To compile the program, do as normal user:

make

This should build the adplay executable.

To install, do as superuser:

make install

This places the executable into /usr/local/bin. You can modify the target path
by altering the makefile.

Uninstallation
--------------
If you wish to uninstall AdPlay, you can do as superuser:

make uninstall

to remove the executable from /usr/local/bin.

Usage
-----
Start adplay with at least one file to be played as parameter. Additional
commandline parameters are explained by typing:

adplay --help

That's all for now. A more detailed doc will follow when i get the time to
write one. Any help is greatly appreciated!
